[NanoMips system emulator / qemu](https://qemu-project.gitlab.io/qemu/system/target-mips.html)

comment.body:
That is a lot of effort.

If you can sponsor this work, contact us.

issue.title: New and improved Python bindings
issue.body:
Re-implemented Unicorn Python bindings while remaining compatible with the original bindings API.

Highlights:
- OOP design for improved efficiency and extensibility
- Pythonic code featuring type annotations to facilitate its usage
- Cleaner code and documented methods
- Lower memory footprint
- Improved Uc resources deallocation

Changes:
- `UcError` now provides additional information, when applicable, to provide the users with better error context (e.g. the target address and access size for invalid memory accesses)
- Intel arch now supports reading and writing ZMM registers
- ARM arch now supports reading and writing Q registers

issue.title: New cs_reg_is_subreg API
issue.body:
This adds a new public API in order to check if a register is a sub-register of another one:
bool CAPSTONE_API cs_reg_is_subreg(csh ud, unsigned int reg_a, unsigned int reg_b)

For instance, cs_reg_is_subreg(csh, X86_REG_EAX, X86_REG_AH) will return true.

I had to add new fields to cs_struct in order to convert between public & private registers. This is needed especially for x86 where Capstone's public register enum doesn't match LLVM's one anymore (on Capstone `next` branch). An existing function does the conversion between public and private register IDs via a table, so I added the reverse table and function.

comment.body:
I think this API is not essential.

issue.title: Disassembler for JVM Bytecode
issue.body: Following on from [this ImHex feature request](https://github.com/WerWolv/ImHex/issues/501), would a JVM bytecode disassembler be a good addition to Capstone? If so, I can work on implementing one

comment.body:
If disasm without any context (ie just raw input binary + info on
arch+mode), then yes this fits the model of capstone.

Before you start, can you post a PoC like example_jvm.c, like those under
examples/ directory?

issue.body:
I have a TriCore port from QEMU to UnicornV2.

This is my first time contributing to a public repository. How should I go about submitting a pull request? 

Also, is there a checklist of things I should provide besides just TriCore support?

comment.body:
Are you based on v5.0.1?

Make sure to have samples/sample_tricore.c, then we will add more testcases
later.

issue.title: Disassembler for JVM Bytecode
issue.body: Following on from [this ImHex feature request](https://github.com/WerWolv/ImHex/issues/501), would a JVM bytecode disassembler be a good addition to Capstone? If so, I can work on implementing one

comment.body:
If disasm without any context (ie just raw input binary + info on
arch+mode), then yes this fits the model of capstone.

Before you start, can you post a PoC like example_jvm.c, like those under
examples/ directory?
